{"updated_at": "2011-12-08T04:14:29Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2011-12-08T04:14:29Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/3057703", "id": 3057703, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3706", "issue_id": 3706, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenseng/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/jenseng", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenseng/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenseng/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenseng/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "bc66e548a86d9635d5d1542080db5665", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenseng/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenseng", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenseng/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/bc66e548a86d9635d5d1542080db5665?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F848ffe097e37ee8768d50dbc688e0757.png", "id": 109489, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenseng/events{/privacy}", "login": "jenseng", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenseng/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenseng/followers"}, "body": "would it be better to just have a :method option (instead of :gist/:gin)? after all, an index can't have more than one method. \r\n\r\nthis would simplify PostgresqlAdapter#add_index, would support all index types (btree/hash/gist/gin), would allow for user-defined index methods, and make the whole thing future proof.\r\n\r\ni personally prefer :type over :method, but that could get confused w/ index_type (i.e. \"\" or \"UNIQUE\"). also the postgres docs generally call it method.", "_id": {"$oid": "523832dbbd3543c15100f925"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3706#issuecomment-3057703"}
